PUBLISHED FOR THE AUTHOR.<br />
1861.
</p>
</div>&#32;<span><span class="pagenum ws-pagenum" id="4" data-page-number="4" data-page-name="Page:Incidents in the life of a slave girl.djvu/10" data-page-index="10" data-page-quality="4" title="Page:Incidents&#95;in&#95;the&#95;life&#95;of&#95;a&#95;slave&#95;girl.djvu/10"><span id="pageindex&#95;10" class="pagenum-inner ws-noexport">&#8203;</span></span></span><div class="wst-dhr" style="visibility:hidden; line-height:100%;">&#160;</div>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r15620827" /><div class="wst-center tiInherit">
<p><span style="font-size:83%;">Entered, according to Act of Congress, in the year 1860, by</span>
</p>
</div>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r15620827" /><div class="wst-center tiInherit">
<p>L. MARIA CHILD.
</p>
</div>
